    "Using Supplementary Cementitious Materials SCMs as partial replacements for cement offers multiple environmental and economic benefits.",
    "SCMs significantly reduce CO 2 emissions and help control the release of air pollutants, such as gases and fine particles, from cement plants.",
    "Additionally, these materials help conserve non-renewable resources by lowering the demand for virgin materials.",
    "They also minimize waste generation and reduce construction costs, offering financial advantages for contractors and engineers [4][5][6].",
    "Figure 1 illustrates the annual increase in cement production, emphasizing the growing need for sustainable practices in the construction industry.The consistent rise in emissions across all regions reflects global trends in increasing cement production, which is driven by urbanization and economic growth."
